title.narrative: CHILD PROTECTION

description.narrative: National and subnational child protection systems and other stakeholders have an increased capacity to generate demand and provide a quality continuum of services in a coordinated manner, and to support protective norms for children and adolescents and their families (including those with disabilities and Roma), focusing on protection from, and prevention of, violence and child separation, which contributes to Access To Inclusive Social Protection, Access To Inclusive Social Protection (Covid), Communication And Advocacy, Cross-Sectoral - Human Rights, Cross-Sectoral - Other Programme Areas, Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement, Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: The social inclusion of all children and adolescents, especially vulnerable ones, is supported by quality, equitable and coordinated health, education and child protection systems and protective social norms.

description.narrative: Due in part to UNICEF advocacy, over €600 million was secured from the European Social Fund Plus;by incorporating scale-up strategies in the 20212027 funding programme to complement state budget allocations – thus laying an important financial foundation for the progressive national scale-up of the MPS. Work aiming to improve the quality of social services at local levels is well underway, such as efforts to increase access to higher education in social work and to create incentives and retention packages for professionals working in remote areas to ensure that by 2030 social services will be performed by fully licensed social workers | Status:On-track | As-of Date:24/01/2022
